<emphasis box="[238,454,280,303]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">Ceramanus centipes</emphasis>
(Taylor ex Gottsche, Lindenb. et Nees) E.D.Cooper.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Etymology:—From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[470,517,312,335]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">cera</emphasis>
meaning wax and 
<emphasis box="[720,790,312,335]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">manus</emphasis>
meaning hand. The name refers to the hand-like appearance of the typically glaucous leaves of species belonging to the genus.
</paragraph>
